<p>As you have seen output  a response on terminal or console is easy through<p> <pre>System.out.println("Render Response"); "standard output stream"</pre> 

 

<p>To read a console input you first construct a Scanner that is attached to System.in </p> 

 

<pre>Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);</pre> 

 

<p>Now we can use various method of Scanner class to read input , For example , the nextLine method reads a  line of input </p> 

<pre> 

    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in); 

    System.out.println("What is your Name"); 

    String name = sc.nextLine(); 

</pre> 

 

<p>Here we have use the nextLine as input might contain spaces .</p> 

 

<p>To read a single word delimited by white space call </p> 

 

<pre>String cname  = sc.next();</pre> 

 

<p>To read an integer use the nextInt() method </p> 

 

<pre>System.out.println("How old are you ? "); 

 

int age = sc.nextInt(); 

</pre> 

 

<p>The Scanner class is in java.util package not in java.lang package so you have to explicitly import this package also.</p> 

 

<pre>    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in); 

    System.out.println("What is your Name"); 

